#### **Question A (14 Marks) `[KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]`**

**(a) Write a complete C program to implement a Circular Queue using an array with the following operations: Enqueue, Dequeue, Display. Use MAX = 5. (7 Marks)**

**Solution:**

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#define MAX 5

int cq[MAX];
int front = -1, rear = -1;

void enqueue(int x) {
    if ((rear + 1) % MAX == front) {
        printf("Circular Queue Overflow!\n");
        return;
    }
    if (front == -1)
        front = 0;
    rear = (rear + 1) % MAX;
    cq[rear] = x;
    printf("%d inserted\n", x);
}

void dequeue() {
    if (front == -1) {
        printf("Circular Queue Underflow!\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("%d deleted\n", cq[front]);
    if (front == rear)
        front = rear = -1;
    else
        front = (front + 1) % MAX;
}

void display() {
    if (front == -1) {
        printf("Empty\n");
        return;
    }
    int i = front;
    printf("Queue: ");
    while (1) {
        printf("%d ", cq[i]);
        if (i == rear) break;
        i = (i + 1) % MAX;
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    enqueue(10); enqueue(20); enqueue(30);
    display();
    dequeue();
    enqueue(40); enqueue(50);
    display();
    return 0;
}
```

**Mark Distribution (7 Marks):**
- Global declarations & structure: 1 mark
- `enqueue` with overflow check using modulo: 2 marks
- `dequeue` with underflow check & reset logic: 2 marks
- `display` with circular traversal: 1 mark
- `main` function demonstrating all operations: 1 mark

