**Q1.** `[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]`
**Define a polynomial node. Write the C structure used to represent one term of a polynomial using a singly linked list.**

**Model Answer:**

A polynomial node stores one non-zero term of the polynomial. The C structure is:

```c
struct Node {
    int coeff;          // coefficient of the term
    int exp;            // exponent of the variable x
    struct Node* next;  // pointer to the next term
};
```

The terms are conventionally maintained in **decreasing order of exponent** to enable efficient $O(m + k)$ addition.

**Marks Distribution:** Definition (1) + Structure (1) + Ordering note (1).

