### ✍️ Model Solution for Q.B(a) — 7 marks

**Structure (2 marks):**

```c
struct Node {
    int coeff;
    int exp;
    struct Node* next;
};
```

**Algorithm (3 marks):** To insert in decreasing order of exponent:

1. If the list is empty, the new node becomes the head.
2. If `newExp > head->exp`, insert at the beginning.
3. Else, traverse the list until `curr->exp > newExp > curr->next->exp` (or end of list is reached), then insert.

**C Code (2 marks):**

```c
Node* insertSorted(Node* head, int c, int e) {
    Node* n = createNode(c, e);
    if (!head || e > head->exp) { n->next = head; return n; }
    Node* t = head;
    while (t->next && t->next->exp > e) t = t->next;
    n->next = t->next;
    t->next = n;
    return head;
}
```

