# 3. Step-by-Step Derivations & Analytical Matrix

## 3.1 Worked Example — Insertion Trace

Let us insert these words (in order) into an initially empty BST:
> `banana`, `apple`, `cherry`, `date`, `apricot`

**Step 1:** Insert `banana` (first word → becomes **root**).

**Step 2:** Insert `apple`. Compare `apple` vs `banana`:
- `strcmp("apple","banana") < 0` → go **left**. Position is empty → insert as left child of `banana`.

**Step 3:** Insert `cherry`. Compare `cherry` vs `banana`:
- `strcmp("cherry","banana") > 0` → go **right**. Empty → insert as right child.

**Step 4:** Insert `date`. Compare `date` vs `banana` → right. Compare `date` vs `cherry` → right. Empty → right child of `cherry`.

**Step 5:** Insert `apricot`. Compare `apricot` vs `banana` → left. Compare `apricot` vs `apple` → right. Empty → right child of `apple`.

### Final BST Structure
```
            banana
           /      \
        apple    cherry
           \         \
        apricot     date
```

## 3.2 In-order Traversal Verification
Following **Left → Root → Right**:
$$
\text{apple} \rightarrow \text{apricot} \rightarrow \text{banana} \rightarrow \text{cherry} \rightarrow \text{date}
$$

> [!TIP]
> Notice the output is in **alphabetical (lexicographic) order** — confirming that in-order traversal of a BST is equivalent to a **sorted dictionary dump**.

## 3.3 Analytical Matrix — Operations on the Above Tree

| Query | Path Taken | Comparisons | Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| Search `cherry` | root → right | 2 | Found ✅ |
| Search `apricot` | root → left → right | 3 | Found ✅ |
| Search `fig` | root → right → right → NULL | 3 | Not Found ❌ |
| Find Min | root → leftmost | 2 | `apple` |
| Find Max | root → rightmost | 3 | `date` |

## 3.4 Complete C Program (KTU Reference Implementation)

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>

#define MAX 100

/* ---------- Node Definition ---------- */
typedef struct Node {
    char word[MAX];
    char meaning[MAX];
    struct Node *left, *right;
} Node;

/* ---------- Create a new node ---------- */
Node* createNode(char *word, char *meaning) {
    Node *newNode = (Node *)malloc(sizeof(Node));
    if (!newNode) {
        printf("Memory allocation failed!\n");
        exit(1);
    }
    strcpy(newNode->word, word);
    strcpy(newNode->meaning, meaning);
    newNode->left = newNode->right = NULL;
    return newNode;
}

/* ---------- Insert / Update a word ---------- */
Node* insert(Node *root, char *word, char *meaning) {
    if (root == NULL)
        return createNode(word, meaning);

    int cmp = strcmp(word, root->word);
    if (cmp < 0)
        root->left = insert(root->left, word, meaning);
    else if (cmp > 0)
        root->right = insert(root->right, word, meaning);
    else
        strcpy(root->meaning, meaning);   /* update on duplicate */

    return root;
}

/* ---------- Search for a word ---------- */
Node* search(Node *root, char *word) {
    if (root == NULL) return NULL;
    int cmp = strcmp(word, root->word);
    if (cmp == 0) return root;
    else if (cmp < 0) return search(root->left, word);
    else return search(root->right, word);
}

/* ---------- In-order display ---------- */
void inorder(Node *root) {
    if (root == NULL) return;
    inorder(root->left);
    printf("%-15s : %s\n", root->word, root->meaning);
    inorder(root->right);
}

/* ---------- Find minimum (leftmost) ---------- */
Node* findMin(Node *root) {
    while (root && root->left != NULL)
        root = root->left;
    return root;
}

/* ---------- Delete a word ---------- */
Node* deleteNode(Node *root, char *word) {
    if (root == NULL) return NULL;

    int cmp = strcmp(word, root->word);
    if (cmp < 0)
        root->left = deleteNode(root->left, word);
    else if (cmp > 0)
        root->right = deleteNode(root->right, word);
    else {
        /* Case 1: No child */
        if (root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL) {
            free(root);
            return NULL;
        }
        /* Case 2: One child */
        else if (root->left == NULL) {
            Node *temp = root->right;
            free(root);
            return temp;
        }
        else if (root->right == NULL) {
            Node *temp = root->left;
            free(root);
            return temp;
        }
        /* Case 3: Two children -> inorder successor */
        Node *temp = findMin(root->right);
        strcpy(root->word, temp->word);
        strcpy(root->meaning, temp->meaning);
        root->right = deleteNode(root->right, temp->word);
    }
    return root;
}

/* ---------- Free the entire tree ---------- */
void freeTree(Node *root) {
    if (root == NULL) return;
    freeTree(root->left);
    freeTree(root->right);
    free(root);
}

/* ---------- Driver / Menu ---------- */
int main() {
    Node *root = NULL;
    int choice;
    char word[MAX], meaning[MAX];

    while (1) {
        printf("\n---- DICTIONARY MENU ----\n");
        printf("1. Insert word\n2. Search word\n3. Display (sorted)\n");
        printf("4. Delete word\n5. Exit\nChoice: ");
        scanf("%d", &choice);
        getchar();   /* consume newline */

        switch (choice) {
        case 1:
            printf("Enter word: ");  fgets(word, MAX, stdin);
            word[strcspn(word, "\n")] = 0;
            printf("Enter meaning: "); fgets(meaning, MAX, stdin);
            meaning[strcspn(meaning, "\n")] = 0;
            root = insert(root, word, meaning);
            printf("Inserted.\n");
            break;
        case 2:
            printf("Enter word to search: "); fgets(word, MAX, stdin);
            word[strcspn(word, "\n")] = 0;
            {
                Node *res = search(root, word);
                if (res) printf("Meaning: %s\n", res->meaning);
                else     printf("Word not found.\n");
            }
            break;
        case 3:
            if (!root) printf("Dictionary empty.\n");
            else { printf("\n--- DICTIONARY (SORTED) ---\n"); inorder(root); }
            break;
        case 4:
            printf("Enter word to delete: "); fgets(word, MAX, stdin);
            word[strcspn(word, "\n")] = 0;
            root = deleteNode(root, word);
            printf("Deleted (if existed).\n");
            break;
        case 5:
            freeTree(root);
            exit(0);
        default:
            printf("Invalid choice!\n");
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```

