# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### **Q1.** `[KTU University Exam - Dec 2023]`
**Define a Binary Search Tree. State the BST property formally.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
A Binary Search Tree (BST) is a binary tree data structure in which for every node $N$ with key $K$, all keys in the left sub-tree are strictly less than $K$ and all keys in the right sub-tree are strictly greater than $K$.
Formally: $\forall N, \forall x \in N.\text{left}, \; \text{key}(x) < \text{key}(N)$ and $\forall y \in N.\text{right}, \; \text{key}(y) > \text{key}(N)$.
This ordering enables search, insertion, and deletion in $O(h)$ where $h$ is the tree height. **(3 marks)**

### **Q2.** `[KTU University Exam - May 2024]`
**What is the time complexity of search operation in a BST in the best, average, and worst cases? Justify.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
- **Best case (balanced BST):** $O(\log n)$ — at each level we discard half the nodes.
- **Average case:** $O(\log n)$ — assuming random insertion, the expected height is $O(\log n)$.
- **Worst case (skewed tree, e.g., inserting sorted data):** $O(n)$ — the tree degenerates into a linked list.

Where $n$ is the number of words. **(3 marks)**

